As agreed at previous AGMs the club aims to retain \pounds1k in reserve. The club's bank balance at the end of January 2020 was \textbf{\pounds1,668.09}. 

\newpage

\section*{Plans for 2020} 	
It has been noted this year that the towing fee paid is not optimally set up to compensate  drivers for the wear and tear on their vehicles, the burden of which (for training or regattas) falls on a small number of members' shoulders. A change to towing fees for the coming year was agreed by the committee such that a fee of 30p per mile can be claimed. This is lower than the HMRC recommended mileage claim for work related journeys (45p), but as these journeys are likely to be taken by someone who was already planning on making the journey by personal choice, this compromise was thought an appropriate use of club funds. It is estimated that it will increase the amount the club pays out for towing by around one third. The increase will come from including payment for journeys under 25 miles (e.g. North Berwick 23 miles: currently \pounds0 will now be paid approx \pounds6.90 each way) and paying more for long distance journeys (e.g. Ullapool 214 miles: \pounds25 - \pounds64.20 each way) while some journeys will be paid less (Queensferry 26 miles: \pounds15 - \pounds7.80).  

Membership fees have not been increased. Expected income from membership in 2020 is between \pounds5-5.5k. 

Expected costs total approximately \pounds4.5k and will therefore be covered by member fees.  
\begin{itemize}
	\item Rental of \pounds150 per month: \pounds1,800 
	    \begin{itemize}
	        \item there may be some additional costs associated with rental space required during boat maintenance
	    \end{itemize}
	\item Skelf \& Sprite equipment upgrade, repair or replacement: \pounds1150 
	\begin{itemize}
	    \item including new oars: \pounds350
	\end{itemize}
	\item Insurance: \pounds650
	\item Admin \& affiliation:  \pounds100
	\item Training support: \pounds350
	\item Towing to events: \pounds400
\end{itemize} 
\medskip

Other sources of sponsorship will be sought as necessary for unanticipated costs or new initiatives. We aim to hold \pounds1k in reserve at the end of January 2021.

Niall Stirling will take over as treasurer this year.

